<subSubSection type="discussion">
<paragraph pageNumber="18">
Roberts &amp; Stewart (1976) in their work on the fishes of the lower Congo River reported the presence of two 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:44F15E82-6680-402C-9D33-22C6AD1A4E2F" class="Actinopterygii" family="Alestidae" genus="Micralestes" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Micralestes Boulenger 1899:86" order="Characiformes" pageNumber="18" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Micralestes</taxonomicName>
in their collections: 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:8EF8299C-6946-4A42-A4DC-08814BC5D16E" class="Actinopterygii" family="Alestidae" genus="Micralestes" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Micralestes acutidens elongatus Daget 1957:126" order="Characiformes" pageNumber="18" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="acutidens">M. acutidens</taxonomicName>
(Fig. 1A) and 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:EF94B4E2-E55F-495C-90F7-93006EE231B0" class="Actinopterygii" family="Alestidae" genus="Micralestes" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Micralestes humilis Boulenger 1899:87" order="Characiformes" pageNumber="18" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="humilis">M. humilis</taxonomicName>
(Fig. 1C). Recent collections in the region also include specimens of 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:6F90A0CB-01EA-484E-B281-41FBBDFAF3C1" class="Actinopterygii" family="Alestidae" genus="Micralestes" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Micralestes lualabae Poll 1967:44, 48" order="Characiformes" pageNumber="18" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="lualabae">M. lualabae</taxonomicName>
(Fig. 1D), 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:A1E37F05-E62F-44FF-85B9-E946DE856C7B" class="Actinopterygii" family="Alestidae" genus="Micralestes" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Micralestes stormsi Boulenger 1902:265" order="Characiformes" pageNumber="18" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="stormsi">M. stormsi</taxonomicName>
(Fig. 1E) and 
<taxonomicName class="Actinopterygii" family="Alestidae" genus="Micralestes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Characiformes" pageNumber="18" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="holargyreus">M. holargyreus</taxonomicName>
(Fig. 1B). In addition to these, a collection made in the vicinity of Inga revealed the presence of a population of diminutive alestid that appears most closely to resemble 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:44F15E82-6680-402C-9D33-22C6AD1A4E2F" class="Actinopterygii" family="Alestidae" genus="Micralestes" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Micralestes Boulenger 1899:86" order="Characiformes" pageNumber="18" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Micralestes</taxonomicName>
but that are not assignable to any described 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:44F15E82-6680-402C-9D33-22C6AD1A4E2F" class="Actinopterygii" family="Alestidae" genus="Micralestes" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Micralestes Boulenger 1899:86" order="Characiformes" pageNumber="18" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Micralestes</taxonomicName>
or to any other species dwarf African alestid.
</paragraph>
